body_text.text:
The term 'buffalo' refers to three species in the family Bovidae. The African buffalo (Syncerus caffer) and the North American buffalo (Bison bison) have yet to be domesticated. On the contrary, the Asian buffalo (B. bubalis) was domesticated around the same time in history as cattle for draft power, milk, and meat (Figure 1
). The domestic buffalo is also known as the 'water buffalo' because of its fondness to cool itself in water (Figure 2
).
